creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: two profiles of a woman, facing R; profile at L is a mostly simple outline with overlaid grid; bust on R is a more detailed and shadowed image
inscription:
Signature, Title, Date, Stamp

-- title in plate, upper right: [EINES WEIBES HAVPT]
-- various numbers inscribed in plate along grid
-- in graphite on verso: B. 220 | p221II | DTAF[...]KW
markings: blue stamp on verso, lower left: Bernhard Keller (Lugt 384); red stamp on verso, lower left: Friedrich Quiring (Lugt 1041c)
provenance: Bernhard Keller (1789-1870), Schaffhouse; Friedrich Quiring (born 1886), Eberswalde; David Tunick, New York; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
signed: monogram and date in plate, bottom center: [1542 / HSB]
title: Eines Weibes Haupt
